* Here are some helpful resources and tools for managing and maintaining an Ethereum validator node:

1) Documentation:
- Prysm documentation - https://docs.prylabs.network
- Ethereum 2.0 specs - https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs

2) Monitoring & Alerting:
- Prysm dashboard - http://localhost:8080
- Prometheus node exporter - https://github.com/prometheus/node_exporter
- Grafana - https://grafana.com
- Uptime Robot - https://uptimerobot.com

3) Logging:
- Docker logs - docker logs -f container
- LogDNA - https://logdna.com

4) Updates:
- Prysm GitHub releases - https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/releases
- Ansible - https://www.ansible.com

5) Troubleshooting:
- Prysm Discord - https://discord.gg/KSA7rKs
- Ethereum StackExchange - https://ethereum.stackexchange.com
- Google Cloud forums - https://cloud.google.com/community

6)  Infrastructure:
- Terraform - https://www.terraform.io
- Ansible - https://www.ansible.com
- Kubernetes - https://kubernetes.io
